title: Design sophisticated logo for an innovative service targeting affluent, savvy homeowners.
description:
We create home inventories that are used as proof for home insurance claims. What's unique about us is the inventory is built on a virtual tour because this method provides a complete visual record of the home and belongings. It’s a digital copy of their home. This visual proof is key to getting a complete settlement from an insurance company if you experience a loss.
We photograph the contents of drawers and cabinets, and the serial number ID plates for major appliances, and place them in the virtual tour providing complete documentation. Even if your home is burned to the ground, you have a complete record of your property, and can build a complete claim quickly, get a better settlement, and get on with your life. That is why our tagline is “Better Preparation. Better Result. Greater Peace of Mind.”
Our target market is wealthy homeowners. Our target cares about their time, money, security, privacy, and value. They are educated, savvy consumers who look to experts when it comes to financial dealings. They want to protect what they have, most aren’t showy or flashy, they don’t flaunt their wealth. They are willing to pay high prices for services as long as they believe it has value. Women are a very important part of our target. They have tremendous influence over household purchase decisions and finances, and they are the second largest group of homebuyers right behind married couples. These are women who are earning more and taking control of their finances. Appealing to their sense of competence and their priorities of home and family is very important to us.
other_notes:
We want our brand to convey security, trust, privacy, and peace of mind. If you ask what we sell, the answer is peace of mind. Purchasing our home inventory service and knowing they are prepared to recover should disaster strike is how clients get that peace of mind.
We want a clean, sophisticated, but not stuffy design that will appeal to the affluent, especially these women. We are undecided if the logo should be literal or conceptual. Show us what you can do!
Our current logo isn’t sophisticated and isn’t the right appeal for our refined target market. We want the main color to be blue. We like the blue that we’ve used, Hex 0071bc, but are not requiring you use it. Whatever colors you use is up to you. Here’s a link to our website, http://www.VirtualHomeInventory.com.
Edit: If you are going to use designs we've like as inspiration for your design, please make it your own. We've received too many designs that are simple variations of others work and therefore too similar.
Also, we've seen a lot of designs that make the word Inventory small under Virtual Home. As a startup all the words in our name are important. Please keep that in mind.

title: Earn the bragging rights of designing a logo for a World Famous cocktail!
description:
The Downtown Hotel in historic Dawson City, Yukon is home to the world famous Sourtoe Cocktail.
Nearly 100,000 people have done the Sourtoe Cocktail...where the Toe Captain drops a mummified human toe into a shot of whisky (in a rock glass) and the customer drinks the shot and once the Toe touches their lips, they have officially joined the club and get a certificate.
The expression is: "You can drink it fast, you can drink it slow, but your lips must touch the Toe".
The Toe is approaching its 50th anniversary in 2023 and is a World Famous tourist attraction , generating worldwide media attention and attracting tourists to Dawson City who want a unique, edgy experience and an instagram worthy story!

Dawson City was home to great Klondike Gold Rush in 1898 and the town is preserved in that frontier town, turn of the century, Victorian style and is a living museum. At the same time we are freezing the dumplings, put them in bags of 12 and sell them directly to consumers. In terms of markets we want to grow from Berlin to Germany to Europe.
The dumplings are of premium quality, with organic certification and regional products. We accompany our products with education to the consumer about the diversity of dumplings.
Our target customer is between 20 and 50, urban, foodie and always on the lookout for the next authentic Asian restaurant in Berlin. He or she is well travelled and earns an above average salary. Our target customer eats consciously and buys either organic meat or eats vegan / vegetarian. He or she considers him or herself a foodie and as open minded for different cultures and cuisines.
